1. INTRODUCTION

Your team has been chosen for a place in the new European League, But
unfortunately you have been placed in the Third Division.

You have £5,000,000 to take your team to the Premier League and challenge
Europe`s best.

This demo version lets you play half a season.  At week 19, the game will
end.  You will have the chance to save the data and use it in the full
game.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. NEW GAME

Once the game has loaded you can start a new game or load a saved game.

When loading a saved game, you will be asked to select which data you want
to load (you can have as many saved games as you want).
Once the data is loaded you will be asked to select your team strip and be
taken to the Main Menu.

When you start a new game you will be asked to choose a team from the forty
European sides. Once you have chosen your team you will be asked to type in
your own name.

Once you have passed that stage, you can then choose which strip you want
your team to wear. There are ten different strips to choose from.

Clearing that hurdle takes you to the Main Menu.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

3. MAIN MENU

At the top of this screen you will see your name, your team name and how much
cash you have. At the bottom, you will see what division your in, the season
number (i.e season 1, 2..etc) and the week number.

You will have the following choice:

                                  A. LEAGUE TABLE
                                  B. FINANCES
                                  C. CLUB RECORDS/HISTORY
                                  D. SQUAD
                                  E. TRANSFERS
                                  F. SAVE GAME
                                  G. STADIUM
                                  H. FIXTURES
                                  I. NEXT MATCH

3A LEAGUE TABLE.

Shows the current position of the teams in your league.


3B FINANCES.

This screen displays all cash coming in and going out of the club.
These are:

Gate Receipts - The home team keeps all cash, except cup games when money
                is split both ways.

Club Wages    - Total weekly bill of players wages.

Transfers     - Total of transfer money coming in and going out.

Sponsors      - When winning a trophy or being beaten, you will receive a
                payment from the trophy sponsors. Payment depends on which
                round you exit. The further your cup run the more cash.

TV Deals      - Every cup game is televised. Payment depends on which round
                and which division your team is in.

Merchandise   - Total of all club merchandise sold in the week. Usually more
                when your playing at home.

Improvements  - Total for improvements made to the stadium.

Club Bills    - Total of the day to day running, stewarding, catering etc.


All details shown are for the previous weeks activities. Totals for incoming
and outgoing cash are also given together with +/- profit.

On this screen you can choose from the following:

                              FINANCES
                              PLAYERS WAGES
                              GATES
                              EXIT

FINANCES.

Takes you back to the Finances screen.

PLAYERS WAGES.

Lists all current team members and their weekly wages.

GATES.

Lists all teams played, the venue and attendances.

EXIT.

Takes you back to the Main Menu.


3C CLUB RECORDS/HISTORY.

Displays club records, previous league placings and cup triumphs.




3D SQUAD.

Displayed on this screen is your current squad. Here you will see:

Players name, players position (G, D, M or A), players rating (1-100),
goals scored and the players value.

You can have up to eighteen players in your squad. Eleven players, three
substitutes and four reserves.

To swap any player about, select the players name, his name will be high-
lighted. Now select another player and they will swap places.

You also have the following choices:

                                    EDIT
                                    TEAM INFO
                                    INJURIES
                                    TRAINING
                                    SUSPENSIONS
                                    SELL PLAYER
                                    TACTICS
                                    EXIT

EDIT.

To edit a players name, select this option then select a players name. You
will now be able to enter a new name for the player using the keyboard.

TEAM INFO.

This displays details of your next opponents. You will be shown both yours
and their league statistics and first team players..
Also given are your own and their totals for strength in attack, midfield,
defence and goalkeeping.


INJURIES/SUSPENSIONS.

If a player is injured or suspended, his name will be shown together with the
number of weeks he will be out. This information will also be shown after
every match. If a player is injured his position (G, D, M or A) will change to
I for injury or S for suspended.


TRAINING.

This is a vital part of management. If your team are not training their
abilities will be affected.

To put a player on training, select this option. The current training for
each player will be shown. Select the players name and their training will
change.

Each player can have training on an individual skill like passing, control
or shooting. Goalkeepers can have handling or diving, etc.

The training will last for approx eight weeks, after that you will have to
give them more training. So keep an eye on everyone.


SELL PLAYER.

If you decide to sell a player, select this option. Now select a player and
any offers will be shown. If you want to accept an offer, select the teams
name and the player will be off. To turn down all offers, select decline.


TACTICS/PLAYING STYLE

This is where you choose your team formation. The players positions are
indicated by their team numbers on the pitch. Selecting any of the six
formations will change the positions.

Selecting PLAYING STYLE will take you to another screen where you can change
the way the players will actualy play. The style does affect the game
depending on which you choose. There is not point in playing an attacking
formation then telling your players to play defensively.
Try and think of tactics that will work, like a 4-4-2, short passing, counter
attack.

There are numerous combinations, some work, some don`t. You will need to
experiment to find the best combination.

Also on this screen, the playing style of your next opponents will be shown.


EXIT.

Takes you back to the Main Menu.


3E TRANSFERS.

If you feel you have to strengthen your squad this is the place to go to.
This screen will display all players available to buy.
The details shown are:

Players name, players ability rating, the division he is currently playing in
and his value.

To bid for a player select buy, then select the players name. You will then
be shown another menu to choose your bid. To increase your bid select +£1000.
To decrease your bid select -£1000. Once you are happy with your bid press the
right mouse button to enter the bid.
Next you will be shown a list of offers from any other interested teams.
The selling team will accept the highest offer.

You can keep buying players until your cash runs out ot there are no more
players or you have a full squad.

Selecting EXIT will take you back to the Main Menu.


3F SAVE GAME.

This screen will display the following:

                                      SAVE GAME
                                      QUIT
                                      EXIT

SAVE GAME.

When saving a game, a file requestor will appear and you will be asked to
select a file name to save your data.

QUIT.

If you want to end the game, this option will take you back to Workbench.

EXIT.

This option takes you back to the Main Menu.


3G STADIUM.

On this screen you can increase your stadiums capacity or change the ticket
prices. The stadium name and current capacity will be shown at the top of the
screen.

CAPACITY.

When this option has been selected you will be given the choice of increasing
the capacity by 5000. This usually takes about five weeks to complete.

TICKETS.

This option allows you to increase/decrease the price of your tickets.

The average ticket prices are as follows:

Premier League : north & south stands - £18   east & west stands - £16.

Division One   : north & south stands - £13   east & west stands - £12.

Division Two   : north & south stands - £10   east & west stands - £9.

Division Three : north & south stands - £7    east & west stands - £6.

Selecting + increases the ticket price and selecting - decreases the price.

If you charge to much the fans will stay away, costing you money. Although
it is possible to increase the price and punish those stay-away fans during
a wicked cup run.

Also, if you charge much less than the standard prices you will probably
have a bigger attendance.

Selecting EXIT takes you to the Main Menu.


3H FIXTURES.

Details the seasons fixtures for your team together with venue and which
tournament (i.e League, FA Cup or League Cup). Also shown is the results of
any games that have been played.


3I NEXT MATCH.

Before kick off, the two teams first eleven players and the match referee
will be shown.

Your fixture is shown at the top of the screen along with the time. At the
bottom half of the screen are the rest of the league matches and their
current score.

During the game you will have the chance to score for your team if they are
playing well. Depending on your chosen style of play for shooting will depend
on how far away from goal you are.
You will see the pitch and your opponents goal. At the bottom of the screen is
an icon with a rotating line. This indicates the angle the ball will be
kicked. Pressing the mouse button will release the ball.
Choose correctly and you may well score.

To make a substitution during the game, press the mouse button. You will then
be presented with your first eleven players and any remaining substitutes.
To change a player, select the name of the player you wish to remove.
His name will be highlighted. Then select a substitute. They will then swap
places. You can also change your formation.

Selecting EXIT takes you back to the match.

At the end of ninety minutes you will be shown the attendance of the match
then the final results.

If you are playing in a cup match and the scores are equal, extra time will
be played. If the scores are still equal at the end of extra time the teams
will replay the game.

After the match is finished you will be shown any injuries or suspension to
your players. Then you will be taken to the Main Menu.

