5. END OF SEASON

Once all games have been played and trophies won or lost the season ends.

The league works on a one up-one down basis. The winners of each league get
promoted, except the winners of the Premier. The teams who finish bottom of
the league get relegated, except the losers in the Third Division.

At the seasons end, you will be shown the final league table. Selecting EXIT
will take you to the honours list.

This screen displays the winners of the FA Cup, the League cup and all the
leagues. Also shown are the teams who are relegated.

When the next season begins your players ability may be different so have
a look and swing that axe if you must. You never know it may just be whats
needed to bring success back to your club.

